6/21/2021

Data Visulation

Production quantities were recorded on a daily and monthly basis. These records were turned into a data set. 2 different graphs were created to visualize these data via R studio. In the first part, the distribution of the total energy produced during a year between the months is shown. In the second part, the energy produced is divided into daily data, where the months are the title. In this way, it has been observed both the ratio of the monthly produced amount to the annual and the days on which the energies produced each month are more efficient.

library(plotrix)
fh2<-aggregate(fh["SolarPV_Consumption"],by=fh["Mounth"],sum)
slices3<- fh2$SolarPV_Consumption
lbls3<-fh2$Mounth
pie(slices3,labels = lbls3,main = "Aylara göre Üretim Miktarı",col = rainbow(15))

ggPlot

ggplot(fh,aes(x=Day,y=SolarPV_Consumption))+
  geom_point()+
  ylab("SolarPV_Consumption")+
  xlab("")+
  facet_wrap(~fh$Mounth)+
  theme_light()+
  labs(title = "Aylara göre Üretim Dağılımı")
